SIMPLE: holding
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Holding
<hw>Hold"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or state of
sustaining, grasping, or retaining.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A tenure; a farm or other estate held of
another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which holds, binds, or influences.</def>
<rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The burden or chorus of a song.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Holding note</b></col> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>, <cd>a note
sustained in one part, while the other parts move.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>holding company</ent>⟦br⟧
